environment.GUI.views

Interface SimulatorView<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type in use by the SimulatorView
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Animated, CommandLine, Graph

    public interface SimulatorView<T>
    The SimulatorView interface is used by classes which deliver information about the status of the simulation.

    Classes that implement the SimulationView interface should implement all the methods in the SimulationView interface.

    Since:
    06/03/2017
    Version:
    11/03/2017
    Author:
    John_Berg, Joshua_Eddy

      • show

        void show(int time,
          T t)
        Show the status of a T object.

        Must be overridden in classes that implement the SimulationView.

        Parameters:
        time - The time of elapsed within the current T object.
        t - The details of the object which is an instance of T status.

      • setEnd

        void setEnd()
        Set the SimulatorView to terminate.

        Flag the SimulatorView to terminate either when:

        • This method is called
        • When the SimulatorView has finished execution
